title: Ukraine Says it Killed Chief of Russia’s Black Sea Fleet
description: As they ramp up attacks on occupied Crimea, Ukrainian forces are repeatedly targeting the fleet based there, a key to Russia’s attacks deep into Ukraine and its blockade of Ukrainian ports.

title: Philippines Says It Removed Chinese Barrier That Blocked Fishing Boats
description: With tensions running high in the South China Sea over territorial rights, the Philippines offered a direct challenge to Beijing by instructing its Coast Guard to haul away a Chinese barrier.

title: Tuesday Briefing: Hollywood Writers Reach a Deal
description: Plus fruits and vegetables for a new climate.

title: Biden Hosts Pacific Islands, With a Rising China in Mind
description: The event at the White House was part of an administration effort to deepen ties with a string of small but strategic nations.

title: Blast at Fuel Depot in Nagorno-Karabakh Prompts Fears of Many Casualties
description: The blast comes as troops from Azerbaijan were moving into the breakaway region that had been controlled by Armenians.

title: Some London Police Officers Step Back From Armed Duty After Murder Charge
description: After a fellow officer was charged with murder in the death of a Black man, several armed officers refused to carry firearms in protest, the Metropolitan Police Service said.

title: Canada’s Speaker Apologizes After Ukrainian Who Fought for Nazis Was Honored
description: Jewish groups demanded an explanation after Anthony Rota, the speaker of Canada’s House of Commons, introduced a 98-year-old veteran of an SS unit as a “hero.”

title: Irish Gymnastics Body Apologizes After Black Girl Is Shunned at Ceremony
description: A video of the medals ceremony fueled indignation online, and drew criticism from the seven-time Olympic medalist Simone Biles.

title: Russia-Ukraine War: Russia Strikes Odesa Port in Deadly Overnight Attack
description: Ukraine said that Moscow had carried out its first major strike on Odesa since the start of a new route to ship Ukrainian grain out of the Black Sea.

title: Dengue Fever Outbreak in Bangladesh Strains Scarce Resources
description: More than 900 people have died this year from the mosquito-borne virus, whose spread has brought rural residents to already overwhelmed hospitals in the capital, Dhaka.

title: American-Made Abrams Tanks Arrive in Ukraine, U.S. Officials Say
description: An initial batch of tanks arrived months ahead of estimates, and in time to be used in Ukraine’s counteroffensive against Russia, officials said.

title: Finland Raced to Join NATO. Now Comes the Hard Part.
description: After decades of going it alone in security issues, Finns are finding that life in a large alliance is complicated, expensive and deeply political.

title: A New Border Crossing: Americans Turn to Mexico for Abortions
description: American women are seeking help from Mexico for abortions, crystallizing the shifting policies of two nations that once held vastly different positions on the procedure.

title: In Romania, the Traumas of a Bloody Revolution Still Cast a Long Shadow
description: People struggling for justice for family members killed in the 1989 uprising say that servants of the Ceausescu regime have blocked any reckoning with the past.

title: Matteo Messina Denaro, Once Italy’s Most Famous Fugitive, Dies at 61
description: A high-ranking member of Cosa Nostra, he was arrested in January after decades on the run. He was found through medical records related to his cancer treatment.
